<br>
I love the small server aspect and I think there's some chance of it working out or I wouldn't be here, but post-50 is going to be a nightmare for the classes that can't solo while trying to get a group.  Also, the language issues are rough.<br>
<br>
I personally plan on grouping only casually until 19.  Then I'll max all the racials and really work on groups.  The 20's are also when classes start to take on definition and grouping becomes much more fun.  I'm hoping to meet and group with lots of people in the 20's and maybe join/start a guild then after I know many different people.  And, most hopefully, setup a regular group to play with up to 60.  Regulars are just amazing incredible fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=morgrist>Morgrist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/19/01 6:07:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=920.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Post 50 /roleplay a problem?</span><hr size=1> Hardly. The problems you're having is simply that there ISN'T a huge population on FV that's in that range right now.<br>
