<br>
Halus, nice of you to turn your LFG on. Hardly anyone else does. Sure, we could say, &quot;everyone should turn it on&quot;, but I assure you that any strategy that starts out &quot;if everyone would just&quot; is doomed to failure. What I'd like to see is more help in the UI for those that do make the effort -- the ones that use strategies that work; ie. people that say &quot;If *I* would just ..&quot;. The forced /anon makes grouping harder. If too many find it more pleasant to be asked (or to ask) class/level when hunting for a group, then let's keep /anon and find another way.<br>
<br>
A default LFG-on would help a ton. I'm not talking about a forced LFG, just a default for when you log on or when you leave a group. You could always turn it off again if you're a die-hard solo'er that never wants to group or to ever be invited into a group. Better still, put the default in the .ini file and let people customize it (start it out as on, though).<br>
<br>
If you are fighting in a partial group, you don't have time to check around for lfg people and lfg people have no way to pick you out as having spots open.  So, what I would dearly love to see, is a way for a group leader to put up an &quot;LFP .. looking for players&quot; to fill out a group. A searchable tag with &quot;/ all lfp&quot; would be a nice start, but details would be nicer eg. lfp 2 x 44-46 bard/sha/enc. <br>
<br>
A method to link up multiple groups for tells and xp during raids would be awesome, too.  If you've ever led a raid, I'm sure you've heard the&quot;my group isn't getting xp&quot; song from first one group then another as you try to balance things out. That and the inter-zone chatter can be hard to parse amidst all the other things going on. Pure-guild events help out a lot on that, but it tends to make the guilds very insular. It's also rough when you end up with 7 or 8 friends wanting to group. Be nice if you could tie them all together.<br>
<br>
EQ is so much fun for a group that a little effort in the interface toward promoting grouping would be an incredible win for everyone. I think it could be done with little effort and could be done in a way that satisfies everyone's RP concerns. Most importantly, it would help out all servers, not just FV -- the only changes that stand a hope of ever happening are those that would help everyone.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrayhateborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gray Hateborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/20/01 1:01:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=920.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm not talking about ..</span><hr size=1> &lt;chuckles&gt; If you got a group complaining about not getting XP on a raid you got some people that dont know what a raid is.<br>
<br>
I had a very pleasant chat with Phiste on this subject and told him at the time that I wouldnt support this change.  With the benefit of added thought and standing back a bit - I still wouldnt support it.<br>
<br>
This server is ABOUT rp and rp is relationships - people who need pick up groups are people who dont form relationships.  People for whom a guild and a list of 20 friends and friends of friends are a wasteland.  <br>
<br>
Here and on my home server (where I am post 50) I group with my in-character friends and guild. I have been in pick up groups when I was in my 20s and 30s and still making those friends - and those were all organised through shout - not LFG - after those levels I didnt pick up at all.<br>
<br>
Phiste argued that it is hard to form guild groups with /role on - which really worried me about the level of community and communication in Resolution, as I told him at the time. <br>
<br>
~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
All that said the sad fact that people left because the combination of anon and languages made finding groups very difficult is absolutely true.<br>
<br>
However - people leaving for that reason has definitley tailed off recently.  Still going on, but less so.<br>
<br>
Also I am seeing a sudden upturn in guild applicants - and the League now has a good balance of the available grouping classes.  I beleive things are settling down and we will have a low population and wonderful server to play on. <p>Lord Regent <b>Gray Hateborn</b><br>
